<!-- FAQ -->
<section class="faq" id="faq">
  <div class="section-eyebrow">Frequently asked</div>
  <h2 class="section-title">Questions we hear<br><em>every week.</em></h2>
  <p class="section-sub">If yours isn't here, ask us on the free call.</p>
  <div class="faq-list">
    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
        Do I need an AFM even if I'm just staying in Greece for a few months?
        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
      </button>
      <div class="faq-a">Possibly. If you're renting, opening a bank account, buying a car, or doing anything that involves a Greek contract, you'll likely need an AFM. It's also required for most government interactions. It doesn't commit you to being a tax resident — it's simply a reference number. We recommend getting one if you're staying more than a month or two.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
        I'm a digital nomad — am I a Greek tax resident?
        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
      </button>
      <div class="faq-a">This depends on how long you've been in Greece in the calendar year. Greece considers you a tax resident if you've spent more than 183 days in the country in a given year. If you are a Greek tax resident, you need to declare your worldwide income. We can assess your situation on a free call and advise on what applies to you.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
        Can I do everything remotely, or do I need to visit an office?
        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
      </button>
      <div class="faq-a">For most services, yes — everything is done remotely. You send us your documents digitally, we handle the rest. For some registrations, a power of attorney signed in your home country (or via a Greek notary) may be required, but we guide you through that process step by step.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
        How do I pay, and is there a subscription?
        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
      </button>
      <div class="faq-a">We charge per service, not via subscription. You pay for what you need when you need it. Payment is via card or bank transfer. We'll always confirm the fee upfront before any work begins — no surprises.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
        What if I've missed previous tax years? Am I in trouble?
        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
      </button>
      <div class="faq-a">You're not alone — this is one of the most common situations we deal with. Greece does have late filing penalties, but they are often manageable, especially for individuals. The worst approach is to continue ignoring it. Book a free call and we'll give you an honest assessment of where you stand and what the next step is.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
