        Who actually does my filing — is it a real Greek accountant?
        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
      </button>
      <div class="faq-a">Yes. MyGreekTax is the English-language front end; all regulated filings are carried out by our licensed Greek accountant partner who is registered with the relevant Greek professional bodies. You get the accessibility of an English-speaking service backed by the compliance of a licensed professional.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
        Will I have to share my TAXISnet password?
        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
      </button>
      <div class="faq-a">No, and you shouldn't share it with anyone. We use a formal εξουσιοδότηση (authorisation) granted by you through myAADE, scoped only to the specific filing we're handling for you. Your TAXISnet account stays under your sole control. This is the same access mechanism Greek accountants use for their domestic clients, and it's the most secure way to delegate a filing without compromising your wider account.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
        Are you a licensed accounting firm?
        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
      </button>
      <div class="faq-a">No, and we're upfront about it. MyGreekTax is an administrative coordination service operated by an EU-registered entity. Every regulated filing is executed by a licensed Greek accountant who is a member of the Economic Chamber of Greece (OEE). Our role is to make the process accessible in English; theirs is to handle the filing under Greek law. Both roles are clearly separated and disclosed.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
        What if my case is more complex than the starting price?
        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
      </button>
      <div class="faq-a">Starting prices on this page apply to straightforward cases. After the free consultation we send you a written quote covering the full scope of work for your specific situation. Nothing starts until you've reviewed and approved that quote in writing. You will never receive a surprise invoice.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
        What's your refund policy?
        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
      </button>
